    dc:creator "Vieira, Leandro M.; Gordon, Dennis P.; Souza, Facelucia B. C.; Haddad, Maria Angélica" ;
    dc:date "2010" ;
    dc:title "New and little-known cheilostomatous Bryozoa from the south and southeastern Brazilian continental shelf and slope" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.276518> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.276518>
    dc:description "FIGURES 2 – 7. 2, Chaperia brasiliensis n. sp., MZUSP 0 274 (holotype specimen), off São Paulo, Brazil. 3 – 7, Amastigia aviculifera n. sp., MZUSP 0 276 (part of holotype specimen), off São Paulo, Brazil. 3, Frontal view of multiserial branch; 4, close-up of paired avicularia at the distal end of the ovicell and one ovicelled zooid; 5, close-up of triserial branch with large frontal avicularia; 6, close-up of biserial branch, note the presence of six distal spines and large proximal avicularium; 7, close-up of two basal vibracula." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/276518/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

